properties.headline: High Wind Warning issued January 2 at 2:01PM MST until January 5 at 7:00AM MST by NWS Cheyenne WY
properties.description:
...STRONG WINDS RETURNING TO SOUTHEAST WYOMING FRIDAY INTO THE
WEEKEND...

The National Weather Service in Cheyenne has issued a High Wind
Warning, which is in effect from 5 AM Saturday to 7 AM MST
Sunday. The High Wind Watch is no longer in effect.

* WHAT...The Ground Blizzard Warning will transition to a High
WInd Warning Saturday morning. West winds 40 to 50 mph with
gusts up to 75 mph possible.


* WHERE...Interstate 80 between Laramie and Rawlins to include
Arlington and Elk Mountain.

* WHEN...From Saturday morning through Sunday morning.

* TIMING...Ground Blizzard conditions expected to end Saturday
morning. Strong winds however..are expected to continue through
Sunday morning.

* WINDS...West winds 40 to 50 mph with gusts up to 75 mph
possible.

* IMPACTS...Mainly to transportation. Travel will be hazardous for
light weight and high profile vehicles, including camping and
tractor trailers. There will be an elevated blow over risk along
Interstate 80 near Arlington and Elk Mountain.
properties.instruction:
Monitor the latest forecasts and warnings for updates on this
situation. Fasten loose objects or shelter objects in a safe
location prior to the onset of winds.

A High Wind Warning means a hazardous high wind event is expected
or occurring. Sustained wind speeds of at least 40 mph or gusts
of 58 mph or more can lead to property damage.

NWSheadline: HIGH WIND WARNING IN EFFECT FROM 5 AM SATURDAY TO 7 AM MST SUNDAY
